Introducing the latest iteration of the Hurley x Moore Aloha collaboration, a collection of surf and sand ready looks brought to you by 5X World Champion, Olympic Gold Medalist, and Oahu native, Carissa Moore (@rissmoore10). With pretty prints and patterns hand drawn by Hawaiian artist, @alohademele, and shot in her super special backyard, this collection comes straight from the heart — with tons of Aloha to spare.

Plus, every purchase helps support the @moorealoha Foundation, an organization started by Carissa to help girls chase their dreams, live authentically, and make time for others. The goal is simple: Moore Love. Link in bio to learn more 🌺💛

🚨 OUR MAUI GOFUNDME IS LIVE IN THE LINK IN OUR BIO 🚨

Hurley is proud to have been a part of historic Front Street in beautiful downtown Lahaina for the last 15 years. With the opening of the second Hurley Store at the Outlets of Maui in 2022, our Hurley Maui Ohana grew to 14 team members.

As the fires have ravaged this remarkable town with its deep history and rich culture, we mourn alongside those who have lost everything. We’ve been working tirelessly out of our Orange County, California offices to send much needed supplies to the island, with multiple pallets already on their way to Hawaii, filled with items generously donated by our mainland community. Among those who have lost everything are our team members on Maui who have our full support as we help them get access to everyday essentials, housing, temporary accommodations, or even flights off the island.

Our intent is to provide as much financial support as possible to our Hurley Ohana and the Lahaina community to help them as they pick up the pieces and restore their town. With your support, our goal is to raise funds to help them survive in the immediate aftermath of this terrible tragedy and down the road as they recover and rebuild.

There are many options for donating to help the people of Maui and we thank you in advance for your time and consideration.

Mahalo,
Hurley
